# Why this game has potential

Most word games teach players to **find words**.

Word Forge teaches players to **understand relationships between words**.

That gives it a stronger educational identity than Wordle or Wordscapes while keeping the gameplay just as simple.

The one thing I'd add in the future is a **personal vocabulary notebook**: every new word the player solves gets saved automatically with its meaning and an example sentence, so the game becomes a growing dictionary of words they've actually learned. I think that would make the educational value much stronger without changing the core gameplay.
